Allen WALBURN, Plaintiff-Counter-Defendant-Appellant, v. CITY OF NAPLES, FLORIDA, a political subdivision of the State of Florida, Defendant-Counter-Claimant-Appellee. No. 06-13138

Non-Argument Calendar

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Oct. 12, 2006. Patrick E. Geraghty, Gerald W. Pierce, Geraghty, Dougherty & Edwards, P.A., Fort Myers, FL, for Plaintiff-Counter-Defendant-Appellant. James Donald Fox, Roetzel & Andress, Naples, FL, Clayton W. Crevasse, Roetzel & Andress LPA, Fort Myers, FL, for Defendant-Counter-Claimant-Appellee. Before TJOFLAT, DUBINA and HULL, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

We find no abuse of discretion in the district court’s denial of appellant’s Fed. C. Civ. P. 60(b) motion for relief from judgment.

AFFIRMED.
